node.text:
The upcoming days I am crossing Europe by train with the #connectingeuropeexpress . This year is the Year of Rail. Using train travel is comfortable and sustainable. The CEE crosses 26 countries in 36 days. I will be in different countries and cities almost every day. It also crosses my hometown Amsterdam, to be seen in this collection. Follow my stories in the upcoming 9 days to see where the trains will take me. I'll also explain how easy it is to travel by train through Europe, how to find the nice spots, how to plan and much more :)
.
#euyearofrail #traveleurope #discovereu #disovereurope #traintravel #amsterdamcity #amsterdamview #amsterdamvibe #livinginamsterdam #visitamsterdam #amsterdamworld #sonyalpha

node.text:
Sunstars used as compositional elements. Some people like it, some people hate it. This collection has a bunch of images each with a sunstar used as compositional elements. Every lens has their own distinctive sunstar. Position the in against an edge and close down the aperture and you start to see it. Do you like to use them in your photos or not?
.
#treebrilliance #sunsetlovers #sunisbeautiful #beautifullight #treephotography #treemagic #treestagram #sonyalpha #madewithluminar #sonypro #sonynederland #sonyphotography

node.text:
Last year right before the lockdowns started in March @danielkordan and I were lucky enough to visit Madeira with a week full of crazy conditions. We found these beautiful trees on a popular hiking trail and spent days and nights capturing them during various conditions.
.
Shortly after that the tree got very popular amongst locals and a few months later popular YouTubers made videos about it. Check @nigel.danson and recently @alynwallace for example, both of these great photographers whose work I enjoy.
.
#madeira #madeiraisland #visitmadeira #madeirabest #madeiralovers #beautifulworld #sonyalpha #treebrilliance #treephotography #treestagram #treemagic #treeoflife

node.text:
Happy World Photography Day. May we celebrate the beauty of taking photos :) . As a photographer I feel blessed to love in a time where technology allows me to capture the world in such great detail. Not only that, but we are living in a super interesting time where photography is more about creativity than ever. Tools that make taking a photo easier than ever, but at the same time that makes taking a photo that stands out more challenging than ever. In the end the most important thing is to simply enjoy being outside and taking photos. So let this day be about that!
.
Photos in this series: Switzerland, Italy, France, Kyrgyzstan, Antarctica, Iceland, the Netherlands, Greenland, Australia, Guatemala
.
#worldphotographyday #beautifulworld #photographyeveryday #sonyalpha #luminar #amazingplaces #tree#treesofinstagram #beautifulviews #beautifulnature
